Jacky, 

I sit here trying to figure out how to sum up who you were and the impact you’ve made on so many lives. The truth is you can’t sum it up. You are so much to so many. When I think of you I think of joy, I think of our little side mouth mumbles to eachother, our impromptu adventures and how much we would laugh. Ugh I’m gonna miss how much we laughed. You were one of my oldest friends and to see you grow but always remain yourself, it’s something most find very hard to do. You made the people around you feel so loved, and so seen. You knew all the right questions to ask to get someone to let down their guard. What a genuine soul you are. And now you’re our Angel. We’ll miss you so much, we love you 🕊

I’ve been trying new things lately. I feel myself growing in ways I never was able to focus on before. I think when we’re younger we let life distract us. We live so much in the moment that I wonder if I was ever truly present before. It was always onto the next for me. But as I’ve continued to live, I’ve learned moments, people, experiences don’t last forever. I’ve lost alot of people not only in my family but friends too. And I think when you lose something you never thought you would, you value what you have even more. You value the present. It’s really a gift to be treasured. Maybe let this post be the reminder you need to let the people in your life know that you need them, you love them, even if ur not seeing eye to eye, let it go. In the big scheme of things I’d rather the time together💗

New year and on the other side of the world lol it’s actually so fitting for this to be where I am at the end of 2023. Similar to a lot of ppl I spoke to, this year was one of the hardest, most eye opening, and still incredible years of my life. So much inside me has broken open. I felt myself become an adult this year. 
  Parts of my life where I wanted to stay innocent and baby like forever I was forced to grow up. Aspects of myself that I had developed a blind eye to - my eyes were forced wide open lol. In all honesty there is a part of me that wishes things could go back to the way I used to see! (Through rose colored 👓) but I’m realizing this is what growing up looks like, feels like, and it is a bit sour 😂 but with the growing pain comes maturity.
 I’m attracting energy now that reflects more of who I’m becoming. I feel grounded, because in moments I used to run to others I now am able to find within. And that my friends is a love I’ve never known before. In turn with that self love, I feel myself able to love the ppl in my life a bit realer a bit deeper. There’s still a lot that I want to improve on in my relationships and the old me would be very uncomfortable with that reality. I was the person that always liked everything so perfect and pretty. But life is raw. And so is real love. 
  So may this year bring us the joy, love and security we all have earned from living thru this past one! lol Happy New Year lovies☺️🫶🏾
